Now, hold on! Hold on! Hold on now!

1425
01:16:20,658 --> 01:16:22,202
Don't you know there's a war on?

1426
01:16:22,285 --> 01:16:24,079
Air raid warden.

1427
01:16:32,837 --> 01:16:34,297
Paper drives.

1428
01:16:34,380 --> 01:16:35,715
Scrap drives.

1429
01:16:35,799 --> 01:16:37,217
Rubber drives.

1430
01:16:37,300 --> 01:16:42,305
Like everybody else on VE Day,
he wept and prayed.

1431
01:16:43,014 --> 01:16:47,477
On VJ Day, he wept and prayed again.

1432
01:16:47,560 --> 01:16:49,771
Joseph, now show him
what happened today.

1433
01:16:49,854 --> 01:16:50,855
Yes, sir.

1434
01:16:51,564 --> 01:16:54,692
This morning, day before Christmas,
about 10:00 a.m.

1435
