Janie, go on. I told you to practice.
Now, go on, play!

1714
01:31:40,119 --> 01:31:41,453
Oh, Daddy!

1715
01:31:46,834 --> 01:31:49,586
George, why must you
torture the children? Why don't you...

1716
01:31:51,046 --> 01:31:52,297
Mary...

1717
01:32:06,353 --> 01:32:08,272
Bedford 247, please.

1718
01:32:08,355 --> 01:32:10,399
- Is Daddy in trouble?
- Yes, Pete.

1719
01:32:10,482 --> 01:32:13,569
- Shall I pray for him?
- Yes, Janie, pray very hard.

1720
01:32:13,652 --> 01:32:15,654
- Me, too?
- You, too, Tommy.

1721
01:32:16,697 --> 01:32:18,657
Hello? Uncle Billy?

1722
01:32:19,283 --> 01:32:20,284
I'm in trouble, Mr. Potter.

1723
01:32:21,535 --> 01:32:22,953
I need help.

1724
01:32:23,996 --> 01:32:26,915
Through some sort of an accident,
my company's short in their accounts.

1725
01:32:26,999 --> 01:32:28,792
The bank examiner got there today.

1726
01:32:28,876 --> 01:32:31,086
I've got to raise $8,000 immediately.

1727
01:32:31,170 --> 01:32:33,672
Oh, that's what the reporters wanted
to talk to you about?

1728
01:32:33,756 --> 01:32:35,090
- The reporters?
- Yes.

1729
01:32:35,174 --> 01:32:38,552
They called me up
from your Building and Loan.

1730
01:32:38,844 --> 01:32:42,222
<i>Oh, there's a man over there
from the D.A.'s office, too.</i>

1731
01:32:42,306 --> 01:32:43,515
He's looking for you.

1732
01:32:43,599 --> 01:32:47,227
Please help me, Mr. Potter.
Help me, won't you, please?

1733
01:32:47,311 --> 01:32:49,146
Can't you see what it means
to my family?

1734
01:32:49,229 --> 01:32:52,066
I'll pay any sort of a bonus
on the loan, any interest,

1735
01:32:52,149 --> 01:32:53,734
if you still want
the Building and Loan...

1736
01:32:53,817 --> 01:32:57,321
George, could it possibly be there's
a slight discrepancy in the books?

1737
01:32:57,404 --> 01:32:58,947
No, sir.
There's nothing wrong with the books.

1738
01:32:59,031 --> 01:33:02,034
I've just misplaced $8,000.
I can't find it anywhere.

1739
01:33:02,117 --> 01:33:05,829
- You misplaced $8,000?
- Yes, sir.

1740
01:33:09,208 --> 01:33:12,795
- Have you notified the police?
- No, sir. I didn't want the publicity.

1741
01:33:12,878 --> 01:33:16,965
- Harry's homecoming tomorrow...
- They're going to believe that one.

1742
01:33:17,049 --> 01:33:19,301
What've you been doing, George?

1743
01:33:19,384 --> 01:33:21,136
Playing the market
with the company's money?

1744
01:33:21,220 --> 01:33:22,346
No, sir. No, sir, I haven't.

1745
01:33:22,429 --> 01:33:24,431
Is it a woman, then?

1746
01:33:24,515 --> 01:33:25,766
You know, it's all over town

1747
01:33:25,849 --> 01:33:28,102
that you've been giving money
to Violet Bick.

1748
01:33:28,185 --> 01:33:29,228
What?

1749
01:33:29,311 --> 01:33:30,729
Not that it makes
any difference to me,

1750
01:33:30,813 --> 01:33:32,022
but why did you come to me?

1751
01:33:32,106 --> 01:33:34,817
Why don't you go to Sam Wainwright
and ask him for the money?

1752
01:33:34,900 --> 01:33:36,527
I can't get a hold of him.
He's in Europe.

1753
01:33:36,610 --> 01:33:38,028
Well, what about
all your other friends?

1754
01:33:38,112 --> 01:33:40,447
They don't have that kind of money,
Mr. Potter. You know that.

1755
01:33:40,531 --> 01:33:42,407
You're the only one in town
that can help me.

1756
01:33:43,659 --> 01:33:46,954
I've suddenly become quite important.

1757
01:33:47,788 --> 01:33:50,457
What kind of security
would I have, George?

1758
01:33:50,541 --> 01:33:53,836
- Have you got any stocks?
- No, sir.

1759
01:33:53,919 --> 01:33:56,755
Bonds? Real estate?
Collateral of any kind?

1760
01:33:57,297 --> 01:34:01,510
I have some life insurance,
a $15,000 policy.

1761
01:34:01,593 --> 01:34:05,264
- Yes. How much is your equity in it?
- Five hundred dollars.

1762
01:34:05,430 --> 01:34:07,266
Five hundred dollars?

1763
01:34:07,724 --> 01:34:10,352
And you ask me to lend you $8,000?

1764
01:34:11,937 --> 01:34:15,023
Look at you. You used to be so cocky.

1765
01:34:15,357 --> 01:34:18,443
You were going to go out
and conquer the world.

1766
01:34:18,986 --> 01:34:23,782
You once called me
a warped, frustrated old man.

1767
01:34:24,449 --> 01:34:27,828
What are you
but a warped, frustrated young man?

1768
01:34:28,412 --> 01:34:29,997
A miserable little clerk,

1769
01:34:30,080 --> 01:34:31,748
Crawling in here
on your hands and knees

1770
01:34:31,832 --> 01:34:33,709
and begging for help.

1771
01:34:33,917 --> 01:34:35,836
No securities, no stocks, no bonds.

1772
01:34:35,919 --> 01:34:39,548
Nothing but a miserable
little $500 equity

1773
01:34:39,631 --> 01:34:41,842
in a life insurance policy.

1774
01:34:42,634 --> 01:34:45,095
You're worth more dead than alive.

1775
01:34:45,554 --> 01:34:48,557
Why don't you go to the riffraff
you love so much

1776
01:34:48,640 --> 01:34:51,143
and ask them to let you have $8,000?

1777
01:34:51,602 --> 01:34:52,811
You know why?

1778
01:34:52,895 --> 01:34:55,189
Because they'd run you
out of town on a rail.

1779
01:34:55,689 --> 01:34:58,901
But I tell you
what I'm going to do for you, George.

1780
01:34:58,984 --> 01:35:02,154
Since the state examiner
is still here,

1781
01:35:02,237 --> 01:35:04,781
as a stockholder
of the Building and Loan,

1782
01:35:04,865 --> 01:35:07,826
I'm going to swear out
a warrant for your arrest.

1783
01:35:08,160 --> 01:35:12,247
Misappropriation of funds,
manipulation, malfeasance.

1784
01:35:13,874 --> 01:35:16,251
All right, George, go ahead.

1785
01:35:16,335 --> 01:35:19,171
You can't hide
in a little town like this.

1786
01:35:19,463 --> 01:35:21,673
Yeah, Bill? This is Potter.

1787
01:35:35,437 --> 01:35:38,690
Merry Christmas! Glad you come!

1788
01:35:39,274 --> 01:35:40,943
How about some of that good spaghetti?

1789
01:35:41,026 --> 01:35:42,694
We got everything.

1790
01:35:53,830 --> 01:35:55,082
Oh, God.

1791
01:35:58,377 --> 01:35:59,670
Oh, God.

1792
01:36:04,716 --> 01:36:06,551
Dear Father in Heaven,

1793
01:36:09,763 --> 01:36:11,723
I'm not a praying man,

1794
01:36:12,891 --> 01:36:15,811
but if you're up there
and you can hear me,

1795
01:36:17,437 --> 01:36:19,064
show me the way.

1796
01:36:19,523 --> 01:36:21,858
I'm at the end of my rope. I...

1797
01:36:23,735 --> 01:36:25,737
Show me the way, O God.

1798
01:36:30,575 --> 01:36:34,246
Are you all right, George?
Want somebody to take you home?

1799
01:36:36,957 --> 01:36:39,334
Why you drink so much, my friend?

1800
01:36:39,418 --> 01:36:42,796
Please go home, Mr. Bailey.
This is Christmas Eve.

1801
01:36:43,297 --> 01:36:45,799
Bailey? Which Bailey?

1802
01:36:46,425 --> 01:36:48,468
This is Mr. George Bailey.

1803
01:36:52,681 --> 01:36:55,517
The next time you talk to my wife
like that, you'll get worse!

1804
01:36:55,600 --> 01:36:56,977
She cried for an hour!

1805
01:36:57,060 --> 01:36:58,353
It isn't enough she slaves

1806
01:36:58,437 --> 01:37:00,188
teaching your stupid kids
how to read and write,

1807
01:37:00,272 --> 01:37:02,858
- and you have to bawl her out.
- You get out of here, Mr. Welch!

1808
01:37:02,941 --> 01:37:04,401
Now, wait, I want to pay for my drink.

1809
01:37:04,484 --> 01:37:06,153
Never mind the money!
You get out of here quick!

1810
01:37:06,236 --> 01:37:09,197
- All right!
- You hit my best friend! Get out!

1811
01:37:14,536 --> 01:37:17,164
- You all right, George?
- Who was that?

1812
01:37:17,581 --> 01:37:20,667
He gone. No worry. He name is Welch.

1813
01:37:20,751 --> 01:37:23,545
- He no come into my place no more.
- Oh, Welch.

1814
01:37:23,628 --> 01:37:25,547
That's what I get for praying.

1815
01:37:25,630 --> 01:37:27,674
The last time he come in here.
You hear that, Nick?

1816
01:37:27,758 --> 01:37:28,884
Yes, you bet.

1817
01:37:28,967 --> 01:37:32,387
Where's my insurance policy?
Oh, here it is.

1818
01:37:32,471 --> 01:37:34,181
Oh, no, please,
don't go this way, Mr. Bailey.

1819
01:37:34,264 --> 01:37:35,891
- I'm all right.
- No, no, you no feel so good.

1820
01:37:35,974 --> 01:37:37,392
- Sit down and rest.
- I'm all right.

1821
01:37:37,476 --> 01:37:39,561
Please no go away, please!

1822
01:37:58,038 --> 01:38:00,374
What do you think you're doing?

1823
01:38:02,459 --> 01:38:03,794
Now look what you did.

1824
01:38:03,877 --> 01:38:06,338
My great-grandfather
planted this tree!

1825
01:38:07,214 --> 01:38:09,216
Hey, you! Hey, you!

1826
01:38:09,966 --> 01:38:13,261
Come back here, you drunken fool!
Get this car out of here!

1827
01:38:21,645 --> 01:38:25,232
Hey, what's the matter with you?
Look where you're going.

1828
01:39:12,070 --> 01:39:13,196
Help!

1829
01:39:14,739 --> 01:39:17,451
Help! Help!

1830
01:39:20,954 --> 01:39:22,789
Help! Help!

1831
01:39:25,417 --> 01:39:27,043
Help!

1832
01:39:29,921 --> 01:39:33,884
Help! Help! Help! Help!

1833
01:39:40,056 --> 01:39:42,350
Help! Help!

1834
01:39:59,284 --> 01:40:01,578
I didn't have time
to get some stylish underwear.

1835
01:40:01,661 --> 01:40:03,830
Wife gave me this on my last birthday.

1836
01:40:05,123 --> 01:40:06,875
I passed away in it.

1837
01:40:10,462 --> 01:40:12,839
Oh, Tom Sawyer's drying out, too.

1838
01:40:16,510 --> 01:40:19,971
You should read the new book
Mark Twain's writing now.

1839
01:40:20,639 --> 01:40:22,516
How did you happen to fall in?

1840
01:40:22,599 --> 01:40:25,769
I didn't fall in.
I jumped in to save George.

1841
01:40:26,061 --> 01:40:28,980
You what? To save me?

1842
01:40:29,189 --> 01:40:30,607
Well, I did, didn't ll?

1843
01:40:30,690 --> 01:40:32,275
You didn't go through with it,
did you??

1844
01:40:32,359 --> 01:40:34,486
- Go through with what?
- Suicide.

1845
01:40:34,569 --> 01:40:37,656
It's against the law
to commit suicide around here.

1846
01:40:37,739 --> 01:40:40,575
Yeah, it's against the law
where I come from, too.

1847
01:40:40,659 --> 01:40:42,994
- Where do you come from?
- Heaven.

1848
01:40:48,166 --> 01:40:51,169
I had to act quickly.
That's why I jumped in.

1849
01:40:51,253 --> 01:40:53,672
I knew if I were drowning,
you'd try to save me.

1850
01:40:53,755 --> 01:40:56,675
You see, you did,
and that's how I saved you.

1851
01:40:57,425 --> 01:40:58,843
Very funny.

1852
01:40:59,052 --> 01:41:01,096
Your lip's bleeding, George.

1853
01:41:01,179 --> 01:41:03,557
Yeah, I got a bust in the jaw

1854
01:41:03,640 --> 01:41:05,308
in answer to a prayer
a little bit ago.

1855
01:41:05,392 --> 01:41:09,229
Oh, no, no, no, George,
I'm the answer to your prayer.

1856
01:41:09,312 --> 01:41:11,648
That's why I was sent down here.

1857
01:41:12,190 --> 01:41:15,402
- How'd you know my name?
- Oh, I know all about you.

1858
01:41:15,485 --> 01:41:17,279
I've watched you grow up
from a little boy.

1859
01:41:17,362 --> 01:41:18,822
What are you,
a mind reader or something?

1860
01:41:18,905 --> 01:41:20,031
No.

1861
01:41:20,115 --> 01:41:24,035
- Well, who are you then?
- Clarence Oddbody, AS2.

1862
01:41:24,744 --> 01:41:26,037
Oddbody?

1863
01:41:27,122 --> 01:41:29,165
AS2? What's that, AS2?

1864
01:41:29,249 --> 01:41:30,333
Angel Second Class.

1865
01:41:41,636 --> 01:41:43,430
Cheerio, my good man.

1866
01:41:47,559 --> 01:41:49,019
Oh, brother.

1867
01:41:51,313 --> 01:41:52,564
Gee whiz.

1868
01:41:53,607 --> 01:41:56,401
I wonder what Martini
put in those drinks.

1869
01:41:58,486 --> 01:42:03,033
Hey, what's with you?
What did you say just a minute ago?

1870
01:42:03,325 --> 01:42:04,951
Why'd you want to save me?

1871
01:42:05,035 --> 01:42:08,622
That's what I was sent down for.
I'm your guardian angel.

1872
01:42:09,039 --> 01:42:11,166
I wouldn't be a bit surprised.

1873
01:42:11,249 --> 01:42:15,587
Ridiculous of you to think
of killing yourself for money, $8,000.

1874
01:42:15,670 --> 01:42:18,715
Yeah, now, just things like that...
How do you know that?

1875
01:42:18,798 --> 01:42:22,844
I told you. I'm your guardian angel.
I know everything about you.

1876
01:42:23,845 --> 01:42:26,973
Well, you look about
like the kind of an angel I'd get.

1877
01:42:27,057 --> 01:42:30,018
Sort of a fallen angel, aren't you?
What happened to your wings?

1878
01:42:30,101 --> 01:42:34,105
I haven't won my wings yet.
That's why I'm an Angel Second Class.

1879
01:42:38,443 --> 01:42:39,986
I don't know
whether I'd like it very much

1880
01:42:40,070 --> 01:42:42,030
being seen around
with an angel without any wings.

1881
01:42:42,113 --> 01:42:45,700
Oh, I've got to earn them,
and you'll help me, won't you??

1882
01:42:45,784 --> 01:42:47,202
Sure, sure.

1883
01:42:47,702 --> 01:42:50,330
- How?
- By letting me help you.

1884
01:42:50,538 --> 01:42:53,333
Yes. Only one way you can help me.

1885
01:42:53,416 --> 01:42:55,377
You don't happen to have
8,000 bucks on you, do you?

1886
01:42:55,460 --> 01:42:57,879
Oh, no. No.
We don't use money in heaven.

1887
01:42:57,962 --> 01:43:00,548
Oh, yeah, that's right,
I keep forgetting.

1888
01:43:01,257 --> 01:43:04,886
- Comes in pretty handy down here, bub.
- Oh, tut, tut, tut.

1889
01:43:05,929 --> 01:43:08,139
I found it out a little late.

1890
01:43:08,556 --> 01:43:10,600
I'm worth more dead than alive.

1891
01:43:10,684 --> 01:43:12,060
Now, look, you mustn't talk like that.

1892
01:43:12,143 --> 01:43:14,854
I won't get my wings
with that attitude.

1893
01:43:14,938 --> 01:43:17,190
You just don't know
all that you've done.

1894
01:43:17,273 --> 01:43:18,608
If it hadn't been for you...

1895
01:43:18,692 --> 01:43:21,403
Yeah, if it hadn't been for me,
everybody'd be a lot better off.

1896
01:43:21,486 --> 01:43:23,697
My wife and my kids and my friends.

1897
01:43:23,780 --> 01:43:27,033
I mean, look, little fellow, go off
and haunt somebody else, will you?

1898
01:43:27,117 --> 01:43:29,744
No, now, you don't understand.
I've got my job...

1899
01:43:29,828 --> 01:43:31,705
Oh, shut up, will you?

1900
01:43:35,583 --> 01:43:38,294
Oh, this isn't gonna be so easy.

1901
01:43:43,174 --> 01:43:45,385
Yeah, so you still think
killing yourself

1902
01:43:45,468 --> 01:43:47,721
would make everyone feel happier, eh?

1903
01:43:49,514 --> 01:43:52,308
Well, I don't know.
I guess you're right.

1904
01:43:53,601 --> 01:43:56,479
I suppose it would have been better
if I'd never been born at all.

1905
01:43:56,563 --> 01:43:59,482
- What'd you say?
- I said I wish I'd never been born.

1906
01:43:59,566 --> 01:44:02,610
Oh, you mustn't say things like that.

1907
01:44:03,027 --> 01:44:07,657
You... Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
That's an idea.

1908
01:44:08,616 --> 01:44:10,285
What do you think?

1909
01:44:10,910 --> 01:44:12,704
Yeah, that'll do it.

1910
01:44:13,371 --> 01:44:14,706
All right.

1911
01:44:17,375 --> 01:44:20,628
You've got your wish.
You've never been born.

1912
01:44:26,217 --> 01:44:29,220
You don't have
to make all that fuss about it!

1913
01:44:30,138 --> 01:44:31,556
What did you say?

1914
01:44:31,639 --> 01:44:33,808
You've never been born.
You don't exist.

1915
01:44:33,892 --> 01:44:35,477
You haven't a care in the world.

1916
01:44:35,560 --> 01:44:38,855
No worries, no obligations,
no $8,000 to get,

1917
01:44:38,938 --> 01:44:40,815
no Potter looking for you
with the Sheriff.

1918
01:44:40,899 --> 01:44:44,319
- Say something else in that ear.
- Sure, you can hear out of it.

1919
01:44:44,402 --> 01:44:46,571
Well, that's the doggonedest thing.

1920
01:44:46,654 --> 01:44:49,199
I haven't heard anything
out of that ear since I was a kid.

1921
01:44:49,282 --> 01:44:51,451
Must have been that jump
in that cold water.

1922
01:44:51,534 --> 01:44:54,245
Your lip stopped bleeding, too,
George.

1923
01:44:58,958 --> 01:45:02,670
What do you know about that?
What's happening?

1924
01:45:04,130 --> 01:45:06,424
It stopped snowing out here,
didn't it?

1925
01:45:06,508 --> 01:45:08,301
What's happened here?

1926
01:45:09,010 --> 01:45:10,929
What I need
is a couple of good stiff drinks.

1927
01:45:11,012 --> 01:45:13,306
How about you, Angel?
You want a drink?

1928
01:45:14,766 --> 01:45:17,060
Come on, soon as
these clothes of ours are dry...

1929
01:45:17,143 --> 01:45:19,103
The clothes are dry.

1930
01:45:19,187 --> 01:45:22,357
What do you know about that?
Stove's hotter than I thought.

1931
01:45:22,440 --> 01:45:26,528
Now, come on, get your clothes on.
We'll stroll up to my car and get...

1932
01:45:26,611 --> 01:45:28,822
Oh, I'm sorry. I'll stroll. You fly.

1933
01:45:28,905 --> 01:45:30,448
I can't fly. I haven't got my wings.

1934
01:45:30,532 --> 01:45:32,242
You haven't got your wings.
Yeah, that's right.

1935
01:45:38,873 --> 01:45:40,208
What's the matter?

1936
01:45:40,291 --> 01:45:43,044
Well, this is where I left my car,
and it isn't here.

1937
01:45:43,127 --> 01:45:44,212
You have no car.

1938
01:45:44,295 --> 01:45:46,422
Well, I had a car,
and it was right here.

1939
01:45:46,506 --> 01:45:48,049
I guess somebody moved it.

1940
01:45:48,132 --> 01:45:52,220
- Good evening.
- Oh, say, hey, where's my car?

1941
01:45:52,470 --> 01:45:54,556
- I beg your pardon?
- My car, my car.

1942
01:45:54,639 --> 01:45:56,933
I'm the fellow that owns the car
that ran into your tree.

1943
01:45:57,016 --> 01:45:59,060
- What tree?
- What do you mean, what tree?

1944
01:45:59,143 --> 01:46:01,229
This tree. Here, I ran into it.

1945
01:46:01,312 --> 01:46:04,524
Cut a big gash
in the side of it there.

1946
01:46:08,820 --> 01:46:12,323
You must mean two other trees.
You had me worried.

1947
01:46:12,407 --> 01:46:14,617
One of the oldest trees
in Pottersville.

1948
01:46:14,701 --> 01:46:15,869
Pottersville?

1949
01:46:15,952 --> 01:46:17,579
Why, you mean Bedford Falls.

1950
01:46:17,662 --> 01:46:21,207
I mean Pottersville.
Don't you think I know where I live?

1951
01:46:21,374 --> 01:46:23,459
What's the matter with you?

1952
01:46:23,543 --> 01:46:26,754
What's the matter with me?
Well, I guess I just...

1953
01:46:29,132 --> 01:46:30,133
Oh, I don't know.

1954
01:46:30,216 --> 01:46:33,219
Either I'm off my nut
or he is or you are.

1955
01:46:34,596 --> 01:46:35,763
It isn't me.

1956
01:46:35,847 --> 01:46:38,099
Well, maybe I left the car
up at Martini's.

1957
01:46:38,182 --> 01:46:40,351
- Well, come on, Gabriel.
- Clarence.

1958
01:46:40,435 --> 01:46:42,186
Clarence. Clarence.

1959
01:46:47,859 --> 01:46:50,653
That's all right. Go on in.
Martini is a friend of mine.

1960
01:46:52,030 --> 01:46:54,699
There's a place to sit down. Sit down.

1961
01:47:01,039 --> 01:47:03,458
Oh, hello, Nick. Hey, where's Martini?

1962
01:47:03,541 --> 01:47:04,626
Want a martini?

1963
01:47:04,709 --> 01:47:06,753
No, no, Martini. Your boss.
Where is he?

1964
01:47:06,836 --> 01:47:09,255
Hey, look, I'm the boss.
You want a drink or don't you?

1965
01:47:09,339 --> 01:47:11,549
Okay, all right. Double bourbon,
will you, and quick, huh?

1966
01:47:11,633 --> 01:47:12,884
Okay.

1967
01:47:16,012 --> 01:47:19,057
- What's yours?
- I was just thinking.

1968
01:47:20,266 --> 01:47:22,685
It's been so long since ll...

1969
01:47:22,769 --> 01:47:26,439
Look, mister, I'm standing here
waiting for you to make up your mind.

1970
01:47:26,522 --> 01:47:28,149
That's a good man.

1971
01:47:28,232 --> 01:47:30,401
I was just thinking

1972
01:47:31,235 --> 01:47:34,405
of a flaming rum punch.

1973
01:47:34,781 --> 01:47:37,325
No, it's not cold enough for that,
not nearly cold enough.

1974
01:47:37,408 --> 01:47:40,328
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute. I got it.

1975
01:47:40,411 --> 01:47:44,040
Mulled wine, heavy on the cinnamon
and light on the cloves.

1976
01:47:44,123 --> 01:47:46,042
Off with you, me lad, and be lively!

1977
01:47:46,125 --> 01:47:49,170
Hey, look, mister,
we serve hard drinks in here

1978
01:47:49,253 --> 01:47:51,005
for men who want to get drunk fast.

1979
01:47:51,089 --> 01:47:54,676
And we don't need any characters
around to give the joint atmosphere.

1980
01:47:54,759 --> 01:47:58,346
Is that clear, or do I have
to slip you my left for a convincer?

1981
01:47:58,429 --> 01:47:59,847
What's he talking about?

1982
01:47:59,931 --> 01:48:03,810
Nick, Nick,
just give him the same as mine.

1983
01:48:03,893 --> 01:48:06,229
- He's okay.
- Okay.

1984
01:48:07,647 --> 01:48:11,234
What's the matter with him?
I never saw Nick act like that before.

1985
01:48:11,317 --> 01:48:14,445
You'll see a lot of strange things
from now on.

1986
01:48:14,696 --> 01:48:16,447
Oh, yeah.

1987
01:48:19,659 --> 01:48:23,287
Hey, little fellow,
you worry me, you know.

1988
01:48:23,371 --> 01:48:26,332
- You got some place to sleep?
- No.

1989
01:48:26,416 --> 01:48:27,959
You don't, huh?

1990
01:48:28,042 --> 01:48:30,670
- Well, you got any money?
- No.

1991
01:48:31,629 --> 01:48:33,256
No wonder you jumped in the river.

1992
01:48:33,339 --> 01:48:36,968
I jumped in the river to save you
so I could get my wings.

1993
01:48:40,847 --> 01:48:42,974
- Somebody's just made it.
- Made what?

1994
01:48:43,057 --> 01:48:44,475
Every time you hear a bell ring,

1995
01:48:44,559 --> 01:48:47,854
it means that
some angel's just got his wings.

1996
01:48:55,737 --> 01:48:58,489
Look, I think maybe you
better not mention

1997
01:48:58,573 --> 01:48:59,907
getting your wings around here.

1998
01:48:59,991 --> 01:49:02,452
Why? Don't they believe in angels?

1999
01:49:04,996 --> 01:49:06,873
Yeah, they believe in them.

2000
01:49:06,956 --> 01:49:10,251
Oh, why should they be surprised
when they see one?

2001
01:49:12,045 --> 01:49:15,298
Oh, he never grew up. He's...

2002
01:49:15,673 --> 01:49:19,719
- How old are you anyway, Clarence?
- Two hundred and ninety-three,

2003
01:49:21,512 --> 01:49:22,513
next May.

2004
01:49:23,806 --> 01:49:26,434
That does it. Out, you two pixies!

2005
01:49:26,517 --> 01:49:28,478
Go through the door or out the window.

2006
01:49:28,561 --> 01:49:30,605
- Look, Nick, what's wrong?
- Now, that's another thing.

2007
01:49:30,688 --> 01:49:32,690
Where do you come off calling me Nick?

2008
01:49:32,774 --> 01:49:34,275
Well, Nick, that's your name.

2009
01:49:34,358 --> 01:49:38,488
What's that got to do with it?
I don't know you from Adam's off ox.

2010
01:49:38,571 --> 01:49:40,656
Hey. Hey, you rummy, there.
Come here, come here.

2011
01:49:44,911 --> 01:49:48,498
Didn't I tell you never to come
panhandling around here, huh?

2012
01:49:55,546 --> 01:49:56,923
Mr. Gower.

2013
01:49:58,174 --> 01:49:59,509
Mr. Gower.

2014
01:50:01,135 --> 01:50:02,887
What... What did...

2015
01:50:03,221 --> 01:50:05,681
Mr. Gower, look,
this is George Bailey.

2016
01:50:07,058 --> 01:50:09,185
- Don't you know me?
- No.

2017
01:50:10,770 --> 01:50:11,979
No.

2018
01:50:12,063 --> 01:50:13,481
Throw him out. Throw him out.

2019
01:50:13,564 --> 01:50:15,608
Mr. Gower! Hey, what is...

2020
01:50:16,734 --> 01:50:19,028
Hey, Nick. Nick.
Isn't that Mr. Gower, the druggist?

2021
01:50:19,112 --> 01:50:21,322
You know, that's another reason
for me not to like you.

2022
01:50:21,405 --> 01:50:24,867
That rum head spent 20 years in jail
for poisoning a kid.

2023
01:50:24,951 --> 01:50:27,829
If you know him,
you must be a jailbird yourself.

2024
01:50:27,912 --> 01:50:29,956
Would you show these gentlemen
to the door?

2025
01:50:30,039 --> 01:50:32,083
Sure. This way, gentlemen.

2026
01:50:37,505 --> 01:50:38,798
Stay out.

2027
01:50:39,924 --> 01:50:42,552
Get me! I'm giving out wings!

2028
01:50:45,221 --> 01:50:47,723
You see, George,
you were not there to stop Gower

2029
01:50:47,807 --> 01:50:49,517
from putting that poison
into the capsules.

2030
01:50:49,600 --> 01:50:53,271
What do you mean, I wasn't there?
I remember distinctly...

2031
01:50:55,439 --> 01:50:57,900
Hey, what's going on around here?

2032
01:50:58,151 --> 01:50:59,527
What...

2033
01:51:00,653 --> 01:51:03,281
Why, this ought to be Martini's place.

2034
01:51:09,203 --> 01:51:10,872
Look, who are you?

2035
01:51:11,122 --> 01:51:13,666
I told you, George.
I'm your guardian angel.

2036
01:51:13,749 --> 01:51:15,501
Yeah, yeah, I know. You told me that.

2037
01:51:21,591 --> 01:51:24,844
What else are you?
What, are you a hypnotist?

2038
01:51:24,927 --> 01:51:26,053
No. Of course not.

2039
01:51:26,137 --> 01:51:28,723
Well, then, why am I seeing
all these strange things here?

2040
01:51:28,806 --> 01:51:33,227
Don't you understand, George?
It's because you were not born.

2041
01:51:33,311 --> 01:51:37,648
- Well, if I wasn't born, who am 1?
- You're nobody. You have no identity.

2042
01:51:37,732 --> 01:51:40,401
What do you mean, no identity?
My name's George Bailey.

2043
01:51:40,484 --> 01:51:42,528
There is no George Bailey.

2044
01:51:43,654 --> 01:51:47,992
You have no papers, no cards,
no driver's license,

2045
01:51:48,409 --> 01:51:51,162
no 4-F card, no insurance policy.

2046
01:51:52,163 --> 01:51:54,165
They're not there, either.

2047
01:51:55,374 --> 01:51:57,710
- What?
- Zuzu's petals.

2048
01:52:03,174 --> 01:52:05,927
You've been given
a great gift, George,

2049
01:52:06,093 --> 01:52:09,680
a chance to see what the world
would be like without you.

2050
01:52:12,016 --> 01:52:14,685
Now, wait a minute here.
Wait a minute here.

2051
01:52:16,562 --> 01:52:19,857
This is some sort of a funny dream
I'm having.

2052
01:52:20,024 --> 01:52:21,859
So long, mister. I'm going home.

2053
01:52:21,943 --> 01:52:24,820
- Home? What home?
- Shut up! Cut it out!

2054
01:52:25,321 --> 01:52:29,367
You're crazy!
That's what I think. You're screwy.

2055
01:52:29,784 --> 01:52:32,453
You're driving me crazy, too.
I'm seeing things here.

2056
01:52:32,536 --> 01:52:34,455
I'm going home
and see my wife and family.

2057
01:52:34,538 --> 01:52:37,750
You understand that?
And I'm going home alone.

2058
01:52:40,127 --> 01:52:42,046
How am I doing, Joseph?

2059
01:52:42,755 --> 01:52:43,965
Thanks.

2060
01:52:44,298 --> 01:52:46,384
No, I didn't have a drink.

2061
01:53:37,601 --> 01:53:40,146
Hey, hey, where did
the Building and Loan move to?

2062
01:53:40,229 --> 01:53:41,230
Building and what?

2063
01:53:41,314 --> 01:53:43,065
The Bailey Building and Loan.
It was up there.

2064
01:53:43,149 --> 01:53:45,026
They went out of business years ago.

2065
01:53:45,109 --> 01:53:46,485
That sailor's a liar!

2066
01:53:46,569 --> 01:53:48,863
I know every big shot in this town!

2067
01:53:48,946 --> 01:53:51,490
I know Potter,
and I'll have you kicked off the beat.

2068
01:53:51,574 --> 01:53:53,034
Hey, Violet!

2069
01:53:54,243 --> 01:53:56,829
Hey, hey! Listen. That's Violet Bick.

2070
01:53:56,912 --> 01:53:59,040
- I know.
- I know that girl!

2071
01:53:59,123 --> 01:54:00,916
Take a walk. Beat it.

2072
01:54:02,918 --> 01:54:04,670
Hey, Ernie! Ernie.

2073
01:54:06,839 --> 01:54:08,716
Ernie, take me home.
I'm going off my nut.

2074
01:54:08,799 --> 01:54:09,842
Where do you live?

2075
01:54:09,925 --> 01:54:12,011
Now, doggone it, Ernie,
don't you start pulling that stuff.

2076
01:54:12,094 --> 01:54:14,597
You know where I live. 320 Sycamore.
Now hurry up.

2077
01:54:14,680 --> 01:54:18,142
- All right. 320 Sycamore?
- Yeah, yeah, hurry up. Zuzu's sick.

2078
01:54:18,225 --> 01:54:20,061
- Come on.
- All right. All right.

2079
01:54:20,644 --> 01:54:22,730
Come on, Ernie,
now straighten me out here.

2080
01:54:22,813 --> 01:54:25,816
Look, I've got some bad liquor
or something. Listen to me.

2081
01:54:25,900 --> 01:54:27,068
Now, you are Ernie Bishop,

2082
01:54:27,151 --> 01:54:28,903
and you live in Bailey Park
with your wife and kid?

2083
01:54:28,986 --> 01:54:31,072
- That's right, isn't it?
- You seen my wife?

2084
01:54:31,155 --> 01:54:34,408
Seen your wife?
I've been to your house 100 times.

2085
01:54:34,492 --> 01:54:37,286
Look, bud, what's the idea?
I live in a shack in Potter's Field,

2086
01:54:37,370 --> 01:54:39,413
my wife ran away three years ago
and took the kid,

2087
01:54:39,497 --> 01:54:41,957
and I ain't never seen you
before in my life, see?

2088
01:54:42,041 --> 01:54:44,835
Okay, well, just step on it.
Just get me home!

2089
01:55:02,353 --> 01:55:04,605
- Is this the place?
- Of course it's the place.

2090
01:55:04,688 --> 01:55:07,942
Well, this house ain't been lived in
for 20 years.

2091
01:55:13,989 --> 01:55:15,950
- What's up, Ernie?
- I don't know.

2092
01:55:16,033 --> 01:55:19,245
But we better keep our eye
on this guy. He's bats.

2093
01:55:36,720 --> 01:55:38,889
Mary. Mary!

2094
01:55:41,892 --> 01:55:44,770
Tommy! Pete! Janie! Zulu!
Where are you?

2095
01:55:45,229 --> 01:55:47,815
They're not here, George.
You have no children.

2096
01:55:47,898 --> 01:55:49,358
Where are they?
What have you done with them?

2097
01:55:49,442 --> 01:55:51,610
All right, put up your hands.
No fast moves.

2098
01:55:51,694 --> 01:55:53,279
Come on out here, both of you.

2099
01:55:53,362 --> 01:55:55,656
- Bert! Thank heaven you're here.
- Back this.

2100
01:55:55,739 --> 01:55:59,034
Bert, what's happened to this house?
Where's Mary? Where's my kids?

2101
01:55:59,118 --> 01:56:00,786
- Watch him, Bert.
- Come on, come on.

2102
01:56:00,870 --> 01:56:02,913
Bert, Ernie.
What's the matter with you two guys?

2103
01:56:02,997 --> 01:56:04,498
You were here on my wedding night.

2104
01:56:04,582 --> 01:56:06,167
You, both of you,
stood out there on the porch

2105
01:56:06,250 --> 01:56:08,586
- and sung to us, don't you remember?
- Think I'd better be going.

2106
01:56:08,669 --> 01:56:10,004
Look, now,
why don't you be a good kid,

2107
01:56:10,087 --> 01:56:11,213
and we'll take you in to a doctor?

2108
01:56:11,297 --> 01:56:13,257
- Everything's gonna be all right.
- Bert, no, listen to me.

2109
01:56:13,340 --> 01:56:15,176
Ernie, will you take me over
to my mother's house?

2110
01:56:15,259 --> 01:56:17,761
Bert, listen. It's that fellow here.
He says he's an angel.

2111
01:56:17,845 --> 01:56:21,265
- He's trying to hypnotize me.
- I hate to do this to you, bud, but...

2112
01:56:22,600 --> 01:56:25,352
Run, George! Run, George! Run!

2113
01:56:27,062 --> 01:56:29,857
- Joseph! Help! Help!
- Oh, shut up.

2114
01:56:29,982 --> 01:56:32,776
Oh, Joseph! Joseph!

2115
01:56:38,616 --> 01:56:41,911
Where'd he go? Where'd he go?
I had him right here.

2116
01:56:44,497 --> 01:56:45,498
I need a drink.

2117
01:56:46,665 --> 01:56:48,959
Well, which way did he go?
Help me find him.

2118
01:56:59,220 --> 01:57:00,346
Well?

2119
01:57:03,599 --> 01:57:04,808
Mother.

2120
01:57:06,810 --> 01:57:08,812
Mother? What do you want?

2121
01:57:10,022 --> 01:57:12,650
Mother, this is George.

2122
01:57:13,025 --> 01:57:14,818
I thought sure you'd remember me.

2123
01:57:14,902 --> 01:57:16,320
George who?

2124
01:57:16,403 --> 01:57:18,239
If you're looking for a room,
there's no vacancy.

2125
01:57:18,322 --> 01:57:21,700
Mother, listen. Please help me.
Something terrible's happened to me.

2126
01:57:21,784 --> 01:57:24,203
I don't know what it is.
Something's happened to everybody.

2127
01:57:24,286 --> 01:57:27,248
Please let me come in,
and keep me here until I get over it.

2128
01:57:27,331 --> 01:57:29,667
Get over what?
I don't take in strangers

2129
01:57:29,750 --> 01:57:32,294
unless they're sent here
by somebody I know.

2130
01:57:32,628 --> 01:57:37,591
Well, I know everybody you know.
Your brother-in-law, Uncle Billy.

2131
01:57:37,675 --> 01:57:39,426
- You know him?
- Well, sure I do.

2132
01:57:39,510 --> 01:57:41,637
- When did you see him last?
- Today over at his house.

2133
01:57:41,720 --> 01:57:42,846
It's a lie.

2134
01:57:42,930 --> 01:57:45,808
He's been in the insane asylum
ever since he lost his business.

2135
01:57:45,891 --> 01:57:48,769
And if you ask me,
that's where you belong.

2136
01:58:00,698 --> 01:58:02,366
Strange, isn't it?

2137
01:58:02,825 --> 01:58:05,744
Each man's life
touches so many other lives.

2138
01:58:06,203 --> 01:58:09,123
And when he isn't around,
he leaves an awful hole, doesn't he?

2139
01:58:09,206 --> 01:58:10,416
I've heard of things like this.

2140
01:58:10,499 --> 01:58:12,251
You got me in some kind of a spell
or something.

2141
01:58:12,334 --> 01:58:14,420
Well, I'm gonna get out of it.
I'll get out of it.

2142
01:58:14,503 --> 01:58:16,297
I know how, too. I...

2143
01:58:16,714 --> 01:58:17,840
The last man I talked to,

2144
01:58:17,923 --> 01:58:20,092
before all this stuff
started happening to me, was Martini.

2145
01:58:20,175 --> 01:58:21,385
You know where he lives?

2146
01:58:21,468 --> 01:58:24,388
Well, sure, I know where he lives.
He lives in Bailey Park.

2147
01:58:27,975 --> 01:58:32,438
- Are you sure this is Bailey Park?
- No, I'm not sure of anything anymore.

2148
01:58:33,314 --> 01:58:36,150
<i>Al know is
this should be Bailey Park.</i>

2149
01:58:36,942 --> 01:58:40,696
- But where are the houses?
